[normal]To
[normal] start this meeting of the Scottish Affairs Committee, we are investigating a couple of things today
[normal]:
[normal] one is the follow up to the report that we produced on the Crown Estate and the other is the question of land reform.
[normal]I will start off by asking our witnesses to identify themselves and tell us their roles and what makes them relevant witnesses for us here today.
[normal]Cllr Angus Campbell:[bold] I am the leader of Comhairle nan Eilean Siar
[normal] 
[normal]but I am also here representing 
[normal]three 
[normal]Island
[normal] 
[normal]authorities today.
