[normal]Cllr Angus Campbell:[bold] I think a starting point, if you take the issues that are going on in Lochmaddy for instance, to do with 
[normal]putting pontoons down
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]The 
[normal]local management agreement 
[normal]was dressed up as being them coming in 
[normal]in 
[normal]partnership; what they are actually doing is giving a loan to the local community, which has to be paid back at an interest rate of about 4% above base, which is very similar to what you would get from a bank
[normal] for a commercial operation
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]Fundamentally, I think we want to be able to see local communities having the right to do things on that land without having to ask for permission
